This paper deals with the security and communication aspects of vehicular networks, which are typically studied in the Computer Science sub-categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a scheme for efficient and secure beacon verification in vehicular communication systems, which involves cryptographic techniques and network protocols. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR, followed by cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SY, and cs.IT.
